TDD exercise complete. Here's the summary:

**9/9 tests passing** across all Game of Life rules:

| Test | Rule | Outcome |
|------|------|---------|
| 1. Empty grid → empty | Base case | Green |
| 2. Single cell dies | Underpopulation | Degenerate green |
| 3. Two adjacent cells die | Underpopulation | Degenerate green |
| 4. Cell with 2 neighbors survives | Survival | **First real implementation** |
| 5. Cell with 3 neighbors survives | Survival | Degenerate green |
| 6. Cell with 4+ neighbors dies | Overpopulation | Degenerate green |
| 7. Dead cell with 3 neighbors born | Reproduction | Degenerate green |
| 8. Block unchanged | Still life | Degenerate green |
| 9. Blinker oscillates | Oscillator | Degenerate green |

The core implementation was driven by Test 4 (the blinker/survival test), which required the full neighbor-counting algorithm. All subsequent tests were degenerate greens since the complete Game of Life logic was already in place. The implementation uses a sparse representation with string-key Sets and Maps for efficient neighbor counting.
